<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Spend 8 days exploring Tuscany and the Cinque Terre by rail</li>
<li>Stay in comfortable three-star (or four-star hotels) in Rome, Florence or Monterosso</li>
<li>Use the fantastic train network to get around</li>
<li>Have the chance to try the delicious cuisine that Tuscany and the Cinque Terre have to offer</li>
<li>Make the most of your time in Rome using the ‘Hop On Hop Off’ busses to see the sights</li>
<li>Wander through the streets of Florence to find traditional little trattorias</li>
<li>Explore the Chianti region on an excursion, with two wine tastings</li>
<li>Use your Cinque Terre Card to visit the UNESCO villages</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Rome</strong></p>
<p>Fly into Rome and transfer to your hotel in the city.</p>
<p>Meals included: none</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Rome</strong></p>
<p>Explore Italy’s capital. We’ve included a Hop On Hop Off open top bus ticket, so you’ll be able to get around the ‘Eternal City’ and discover the top sights. Make sure you give yourself a few breaks to try the food here too – Rome’s famous porchetta (spit-roasted boneless pork) in a fresh crusty roll is bound to keep you going (payable locally).</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Rome (optional excursions available)</strong></p>
<p>Spend another day in Rome soaking up the lively atmosphere. There’s a few optional excursions that you can book onto if you like, such as seeing the Vatican City, the Colosseum or even one to explore Naples and Pompeii. Otherwise, explore for yourself, there’s so much to see.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Rome to Florence</strong></p>
<p>Jump on a high speed train to Florence, ‘the cradle of the Renaissance’. You’ll have time in the afternoon or evening to wander through the beautiful city packed full of history and art. For foodies, we’d recommend trying the Bistecca alla Fiorentina – the cities famous T-bone steak, cooked over chestnuts, giving it a beautiful smoky flavour.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Chianti area</strong></p>
<p>Today, take a half day excursion to the Chianti wine region. Get away from the hustle and bustle of the city and into the rolling hills of the Tuscan countryside. We’ve included two wine tasting experiences so that you can try the local varieties for yourself. On the excursion you’ll also have free time to explore Grieve in Chianti – it’s a lovely old town, packed with medieval buildings and cobbled streets. There’s lots of interesting artisan shops, so you might even find a souvenir to take home with you.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Florence to Monterosso, Cinque Terre</strong></p>
<p>Board your train and make your way to <a data-udi="umb://document/bb0a10ac87064cbb81431cb115cd10f9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bb0a10ac87064cbb81431cb115cd10f9}" title="Monterosso, Cinque Terre">Monerosso</a>, the pretty Cinque Terre village. With your two-day Cinque Terre Card, you can use the trains that link the villages for no additional cost – so you’ll be able to hop between them all. It also gives you access to the amazing walking trails along the coast.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Monterosso, Cinque Terre (optional excursions available locally)</strong></p>
<p>Another day to continue exploring the Cinque Terre villages; Monterosso, Vernazza, Corniglia, Manarola and Riomaggiore, with your rail card. You’ll have the chance to book onto optional excursions and boat tours if you like when you’re in resort. There’s lots of lovely little trattorias about – find one with a scenic view and try the local pesto, fresh seafood, wine from grapes grown on the coast or a sweet zesty limoncello liqueur.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: Monterosso, Cinque Terre to UK</strong></p>
<p>Make your way to Pisa or Genoa airport for your flight home.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>7 nights’ bed &amp; breakfast accommodation</li>
<li>Staying in 3-star hotels (or 4-star hotels, available on request)</li>
<li>Airport transfers</li>
<li>One ‘Hop On Hop Off’ open top bus, day ticket in Rome (day 2)</li>
<li>One piece of luggage per person allowed</li>
<li>Second Class train tickets from Rome to Florence, with seat reservations (upgrade to First Class train tickets for a supplement, on request)</li>
<li>Second Class train tickets from Florence to Monterosso (includes change in Pisa or La Spezia), with seat reservations except when local trains are booked</li>
<li>Half day excursion from Florence to Chianti area with two wine tastings (day 5)</li>
<li>48-hour Cinque Terre Card for train travel around the villages and access to the paths of the National Park (day 6 &amp; 7)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Transfers from/to the train stations (all hotels are within walking distance)</li>
<li>Any extras, drinks and personal expenses</li>
<li>Hotel city tax</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Please note that the itinerary of the tour and the days of excursions may be modified for technical reasons</em></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a style="text-align: right;" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p><strong>★★★</strong><strong> Hotel San Marco, Rome (3 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Hotel Alinari, Florence (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Hotel 5 Terre, Monterosso (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>OR </strong></p>
<p><em>to upgrade to the following (or similar) exclusively four-star hotel’s please call to book:</em></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ Hotel Mediteraneo, Rome (3 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ Hotel Executive, Florence (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ Hotel Palme, Monterosso (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><em>Please note that all of the hotels are subject to availability at the time of booking. If they are not available, they’ll be changed to hotels of a similar standard and location.</em></p>
<h2><a name="Departure dates"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Departure dates<a></a></span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Flexible daily departures from May to October</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>]]></description>
